## 📈 Admin: Exporting Student Data

You can easily export every user's progress and points per week into an Excel-compatible CSV file without touching the frontend codebase.

### Step 1: Database Permission (One-time setup)
Run the following in your Supabase Dashboard -> SQL Editor to allow the export script to read all users:
```sql
CREATE POLICY "Allow read all profiles" ON public.profiles FOR SELECT USING (true);
CREATE POLICY "Allow read all progress" ON public.user_progress FOR SELECT USING (true);
```

### Step 2: Run the Exporter
Open your terminal in the project folder and run:
```bash
python export_data.py
```
This will securely fetch cloud data and generate a file like `SkillBuilder_Advanced_Export_2026-04-24_15-30-00.csv` in your folder. Double-click it to open in Excel perfectly formatted!

